WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.413
Shh—look closely.

2
00:00:01.413 --> 00:00:03.241
Two skaters are still.

3
00:00:03.241 --> 00:00:04.737
Watch their hands.

4
00:00:04.737 --> 00:00:08.311
They press, then both
platforms roll apart.

5
00:00:08.311 --> 00:00:09.890
Freeze the picture.

6
00:00:09.890 --> 00:00:11.386
Point to the pair.

7
00:00:11.386 --> 00:00:13.464
Where did the pushes act?

8
00:00:16.701 --> 00:00:20.759
A force is a push or pull
during an interaction.

9
00:00:20.759 --> 00:00:22.534
Skater A pushes on B.

10
00:00:22.534 --> 00:00:24.479
At once, B pushes on A.

11
00:00:24.479 --> 00:00:29.720
One interaction gives two forces,
acting on different objects.

12
00:00:29.720 --> 00:00:31.749
Watch the contact again.

13
00:00:34.986 --> 00:00:36.143
Read the labels.

14
00:00:36.143 --> 00:00:39.759
A on B belongs on B, because
B receives that push.

15
00:00:39.759 --> 00:00:41.205
B on A belongs on A.

16
00:00:41.205 --> 00:00:44.459
The arrows are equal
and point opposite ways.

17
00:00:44.459 --> 00:00:45.327
Two objects.

18
00:00:45.327 --> 00:00:46.122
Two forces.

19
00:00:49.359 --> 00:00:51.304
Now compare the evidence.

20
00:00:51.304 --> 00:00:53.016
Before contact: still.

21
00:00:53.016 --> 00:00:55.195
After contact: moving apart.

22
00:00:55.195 --> 00:00:56.206
What changed?

23
00:00:56.206 --> 00:00:57.218
Their motion.

24
00:00:57.218 --> 00:01:01.886
We cannot see a force floating
by itself, but we can observe

25
00:01:01.886 --> 00:01:04.143
what the interaction changed.

26
00:01:07.380 --> 00:01:11.794
Ooh, careful—many scientists
think the push rides inside the

27
00:01:11.794 --> 00:01:12.309
skater.

28
00:01:12.309 --> 00:01:13.192
Let’s check.

29
00:01:13.192 --> 00:01:15.767
Hands touch: contact
arrows appear.

30
00:01:15.767 --> 00:01:18.269
Hands separate:
the arrows vanish.

31
00:01:18.269 --> 00:01:22.536
On this low-friction track,
the skaters keep gliding while

32
00:01:22.536 --> 00:01:24.228
other forces still act.

33
00:01:27.465 --> 00:01:29.845
Contact forces can push or pull.

34
00:01:29.845 --> 00:01:31.779
A hand pushes a cart away.

35
00:01:31.779 --> 00:01:34.011
A rope pulls a trolley closer.

36
00:01:34.011 --> 00:01:37.433
Name each pair: hand on
cart; rope on trolley.

37
00:01:37.433 --> 00:01:40.929
One object alone is not
a complete explanation.

38
00:01:44.165 --> 00:01:45.904
Keep your eye on the gap.

39
00:01:45.904 --> 00:01:49.174
These magnets never touch,
yet both carts move.

40
00:01:49.174 --> 00:01:51.192
That is non-contact evidence.

41
00:01:51.192 --> 00:01:54.810
Earth also pulls a falling
book without touching it.

42
00:01:54.810 --> 00:01:56.549
Again: which two objects?

43
00:01:59.786 --> 00:02:00.735
Quick check.

44
00:02:00.735 --> 00:02:02.871
Which two objects interact?

45
00:02:02.871 --> 00:02:04.295
Are they touching?

46
00:02:04.295 --> 00:02:06.035
Foot on ball: contact.

47
00:02:06.035 --> 00:02:08.408
Magnet on magnet: non-contact.

48
00:02:08.408 --> 00:02:10.543
Earth on book: non-contact.

49
00:02:10.543 --> 00:02:14.498
Strength does not choose
the label; touching does.

50
00:02:17.735 --> 00:02:19.846
Let’s test two pushes fairly.

51
00:02:19.846 --> 00:02:20.646
Same carts.

52
00:02:20.646 --> 00:02:21.447
Same floor.

53
00:02:21.447 --> 00:02:22.829
Same starting line.

54
00:02:22.829 --> 00:02:26.250
We change only the push,
then measure distance.

55
00:02:26.250 --> 00:02:30.544
Change several things, and the
evidence cannot tell us what

56
00:02:30.544 --> 00:02:31.199
mattered.

57
00:02:34.436 --> 00:02:38.527
A tempting idea: the ball keeps
moving, so the kick must be

58
00:02:38.527 --> 00:02:39.221
inside it.

59
00:02:39.221 --> 00:02:40.053
Let’s check.

60
00:02:40.053 --> 00:02:42.896
Foot touches ball:
the contact push acts.

61
00:02:42.896 --> 00:02:44.838
Foot leaves: that push ends.

62
00:02:44.838 --> 00:02:46.363
The ball keeps moving.

63
00:02:46.363 --> 00:02:49.484
Interaction first;
changed motion afterwards.

64
00:02:52.721 --> 00:02:53.860
Final prediction.

65
00:02:53.860 --> 00:02:57.680
Two magnet carts start still
with a gap, then move apart.

66
00:02:57.680 --> 00:03:00.763
Which observations support
a non-contact push?

67
00:03:00.763 --> 00:03:01.903
Hold your answer.

68
00:03:01.903 --> 00:03:05.589
The gap stays visible, both
motions change, and no hand

69
00:03:05.589 --> 00:03:06.929
touches either cart.

70
00:03:10.166 --> 00:03:12.549
You have the physicist’s move.

71
00:03:12.549 --> 00:03:13.661
Name the pair.

72
00:03:13.661 --> 00:03:15.727
Decide: touch or no touch.

73
00:03:15.727 --> 00:03:18.507
Use a change in
motion as evidence.

74
00:03:18.507 --> 00:03:22.082
A force is not hidden
stuff inside an object.

75
00:03:22.082 --> 00:03:23.750
It is an interaction.

